"@wideofthemark_ was created out of a hunger for a motorcycle adventure in its purest form. Mixing the things we love most in life, Motorcycles, and Films. We built adventure bikes out of everyday commuters to handle harsh terrain, packed our camping gear, and went riding for 2 weeks. Our only goal was a rough road map of some of the most testing terrain Tasmania had to offer."

Visit www.wideofthemark.com.au to watch the full film and for more information.

Make a difference, DONATE  to @wavesforwater AND get a chance to WIN a custom @harleydavidson Forty Eight café racer - link in bio or visit www.croig.co for more info.

•
Dear Open Road,

There was a time when I couldn’t imagine my life without you, but the days have felt longer since our last bout and I’m no longer windswept. I wonder if you’d recognize me.

I remember ...
Your radiating heat that kept me warm after tough battles with the wind. Your distinct aroma of gravel and oil.
Your bumps and scars that made me feel we weren’t so different.

You are ...
A shelter to those with no home.
A track for those who feel safer on the run.
A challenge for the wild at heart.
A teacher for the prideful and a mentor to the humble. You are no one’s to tame, and I am -
.
Forever yours,
Rider
.
.

Back by popular demand, more movies for you watch during your quarantine thanks to @hawk_ryder. Enjoy and stay safe everyone! <Watch the IGTV video to skip to other scenes>
.
1) Terminator 2: Judgement Day (1991)
1991 Harley-Davidson FLSTF Fat Boy 
The T-800 had its pick of various bikes/cars outside of the biker bar where it made its first appearance, finally settling on the Fat Boy which made its debut in Harley’s lineup the year prior. The actual screen used bike last sold at auction in 2018 for $480,000.

2) The Matrix: Reloaded (2003)
2001 Ducati 996
To commemorate this scene (and cash in big time) Ducati partnered with the film to release a limited run of Matrix Edition 998 bikes. Despite the movie actually featuring a 996, by the time the film was released, Ducati had replaced the 996 with the 998, hence the disparity. The only differences between the standard & the “Matrix Edition“ were cosmetic, the ME was painted in a dark green livery like the film bike, finished off with Matrix Reloaded decals and the bikes production number on the tank.

3) The Place Beyond the Pines (2012)
93-98 Honda XR650L 
Goslings character spends the bulk of his screen time on a DR-Z400 that gets chopped up and scrapped after a few successful robberies. The final chase scene takes place on a mostly de-badged late 90’s Honda XR650L.

4) Mission Impossible: Fallout (2018)
2018 BMW R nine T Scrambler
Though many fans push that this was the “pure” model it’s actually the scrambler model with a subdued gray paint scheme. The identifying features include the fork gaiters, high exhaust, toothed footpegs, and solo saddle.

5) Skyfall (2012)
2012 Honda CRF250R
The stunt crew “dressed” both bikes in the opening chase scene to be as non-descript as possible but they are a matching pair of 2012 Honda CRF250R’s. Fun fact: Multiple world record holder, inventor and stuntman extraordinaire @robbiemaddison is in the saddle as the “Bond” stunt double on this no holds barred race across the rooftops of Istanbul, Turkey.
